# Invariants & contracts
  @invariant  sole truth for valid keys; in-code access raises on unknowns, loaded unknowns pruned  @ 3
  @invariant  owns cache: reads deep-clone out, writes deep-clone in; callers never alias cm state  @ 4
  @invariant  5-tier merge: global→project→track→take→transient; most-specific wins, else defaults  @ 5
  @invariant  transient tier never persists (saver is a no-op) and resets to {} on every refreshCache  @ 6
  @invariant  declarations is ordered array-of-pairs; nil-default keys coexist with non-nil defaults  @ 7
  @invariant  track/take tiers require REAPER context; without it loaders return {}, savers error  @ 8
  @contract  caches lazy: first getter triggers refreshCache; setContext/setTrack refresh eagerly  @ 304
  @contract  no take context drops track too (track derived from take in setContext)  @ 305

